cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the theory and optimization of neural networks, which are central topics in machine learning. The paper discusses the distance between two neural networks and proposes a new optimization algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the stability of learning, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper's focus on optimization and algorithms also suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's application to language transformers suggests the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
